reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The bathroom doors did not offer much privacy.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard King Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Everyone was helpful, warm and professional.   We needed a taxi at 4am when a few Ubers canceled in a row (we forgot how challenging Ubers can be early morn in SF) and the gentleman at the front desk called and helped flag down the taxi.   Absolutely saved us / we were traveling for our honeymoon.  Your team made our stay enjoyable - thank you so much!

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard King Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The hotel staff were great and it was relatively affordable considering it's in the middle of Fisherman's Wharf. The room was bigger than I expected and very comfortable, the staff was always helpful, and there were several cafes within 5 minutes walking distance for breakfast. If I'm back in San Francisco I would stay at the Hyatt.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Half the usualy hotel facilities were closed due to the covid re-opening. You should keep that in mind for the foreseeable future. Also most of the entertainment, bars, and nightclub experiences are in different districts but if you want a high end and quiet place to sleep that's near the ferries to Alcatraz and Angel Island this is for you.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard King Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Location was good.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Parking is a pain.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard King Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: My husband and I stayed here for our honeymoon in SF and were very pleased with our stay. The hotel was clean and staff were very friendly. We arrived a few hours before check in and were able to get in early because they had a room available. Which was nice so we didn’t have to drag our luggage around the city waiting for 5pm. We were within walking distance of restaurants, drugstores, grocery stores, etc. If we needed to Uber or Lyft somewhere farther, it wasn’t too expensive and the drivers picked us up right at the front of the hotel where the hotel had seating available, so that was convenient. The area felt relatively safe, we were not out very late though. We would stay here again!
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Only downside for us was not having a microwave in our room! With all the wonderful food in SF it was a bummer to bring leftovers back to the hotel only to discover we couldn’t warm them up.

It was marketed as a farm to table, higher-end, and food-allergen knowledgeable restaurant but we found none of that to be the case. The room was also very underwhelming- cleaner than most hotel rooms but small, very cramped and needing maintenance (ie., tun glaze was chipping off very badly, carpet was sticky…)

The luggage elevator was on the main floor and everyone on the lower would use the luggage elevator seeing that I was waiting to use it. I know they saw me because they were originally waiting behind me for the luggage elevator. It took about five tries to get on the elevator before my husband went to the lower level to save the elevator for me and our baby in the stroller. 
The only parking lot was offsite 1 1/2 blocks away and the only available parking we found was on the roof.  We had to carry the stroller down three stairs to access the elevator.

reviews_list.Room_Type: King Room with City View
reviews_list.Main_Review: There were pluses and minuses to our stay. I would only stay again if I was not bringing our dog.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The food i ordered was nice and hot and very flavorful. The bed was comfy with good quality linens and nice fluffy pillows. Loved the real stone used in the bathroom. The bathroom was a nice size and the blackout curtains did their thing. The artwork throughout the property was thoughtful and nice to look at. The soaps and shampoos were great. I'd buy the Bee Kind brand.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: I asked for a room away from the stairs and elevators, but not too far away as we had a puppy with us and we needed to take her out often to go. Unfortunately. We were the furthest away from the elevators and didn't find the stairs.  // the vent in the bathroom was small and weak.// was unhappy that a 4 star hotel did not have a microwave, and it had a useless half deep mini fridge.  Also, the hallway carpets really needed to be spot steam cleaned. I could easily see stains on the carpet. Lastly, this is marketed as a pet friendly hotel, but they are not close enough to any real patch of green. There's no reason that part of their front area couldn't provide a 10 x 10 foot patch of lawn for the dogs. Not all dogs or their people want to walk or drive to the closest park when the dog needs to go.

reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: It was a bit loud. I’m not sure if they were deep cleaning or what, but there were doors opening and closing, furniture being moved around, and vacuums or carpet cleaners being run until nearly 11 PM

reviews_list.Room_Type: Two Double Beds with Courtyard View
reviews_list.Main_Review: Friendly staff and clean comfortable rooms but amenities are misrepresented.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Comfortable clean rooms and helpful friendly staff.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: There were a few surprises that added to cost or lowered the values that I found misleading and irritating.  Parking costs $45 a night and the pool ended up being closed.  We chose this hotel because it had a pool.  This felt like false advertising as similar hotels without a pool cost $50 less per night.  If restaurants across the country can easily amend their online presence to communicate altered business operations in light of COVID, why can’t this hotel?

reviews_list.Room_Type: King/Double Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Location was great. Property was clean.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Lack of parking was a problem. Was under the impression when booking, that parking would be available.

reviews_list.Room_Type: King Room with Courtyard View
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Location, location, location. Even tho the hotel isnt in Downtown, its still very close to other tourist points such as Pier 39, the chocolate factory, the cable cars, etc. There's a restaurant in the premises (i didnt try it so i wouldnt know how is it). There's a breakfast restaurant right across the hotel, a 7eleven 5 minutes walk. The people at the front desk stuff are amazing, very friendly and charming. The entrance hall is nice. There's a room where you can buy sandwiches, late night snacks, juices, sodas, etc. There's a pool but i didnt use it. I saw a gym as well which I didnt use either. The beds were REALLY comfy and clean. I called to see if I could extend the check out and the girl at the front desk extended for another hour and a half. Im telling you, those people are very well trained and super nice.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Before I write this, keep in mind that im the kind of person that ALWAYS try to find the good in every situation, even when the situation is bad. Let me start saying that I have nothing bad to say about the front desk people, they are amazing, these negative reviews are towards the hotel itself. 1. I thought it was very expensive for what it is. I know it is San Francisco and everything is expensive there (I live in Los Angeles, its the same here) but carpet in the room and all the halls ? C'mon, this is 20222. The pressure on the faucet bathroom wasnt strong enough that it took me 10 minutes to rinse off my face after washing it. 3. This isnt that bad, but if you are thinking on reheating food, forget about it. No microwave in the room. 4. The valet parking is $62 a day but this is the norm in San Francisco, so I guess this isnt a bad thing about the hotel because whatever you go, you'll have to pay outrageous prices for parking. In general, I thought the price was really high for what the hotel has to offer. And if you ask me if I'd stay here again, the answer is no.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: It was a decent location albeit very touristy. The bed was comfortable. Thats about all the good I have to say for this hotel.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: I have traveled occassionally during COVID and only the lazy and excuse-driven hotels are using COVID to not fulfill any basic tasks that can help the guest enjoy their stay. The Hyatt front desk was hostile and non-amenable to any requests with always the same excuse - oh its covid we can't do that right now. EG: I was in the middle of a work meeting and had lunch delivered to the hotel because I couldn't leave and because the hotel has no restaurant open on-site (again because of covid). The front desk would not let the delivery person drop off my order to my room - because of covid - they had to leave it up front. I asked the front desk to have a bellman bring it to my room because I was in the middle of a meeting - they said no, because of covid. Explain that to me? I had to let my food sit out front for 40+ minutes around other guests while I finished my meeting because of the hotel's staff. I thought the customer is always right and it's called "hospitality" for a reason. It was also my birthday weekend which I told them and they tried to charge me $75 to put a birthday gift of wine and flowers in my room - which I didn't ask for btw but why would I pay $75 for a gift for myself? Won't be back here again.

reviews_list.Room_Type: King Room with Courtyard View
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Breakfast was good but super expensive.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Hotel is in a great location right by the fisherman’s wharf. However,  the hotel does not offer parking on site so guests have to park two blocks away from the hotel. It’s not a far walk, but with kids and a lot of stuff it became a huge hassle. The room was okay. Not worth the 200 a night you pay to stay here. I felt like the room was setup more for business people traveling, was not as family friendly as I had hoped. There is no microwave in the room. My family doesn’t typically use microwaves, but again when you’re traveling with kids, it’s nice to have. Plus it’s pretty standard these days for hotel rooms to have one. Especially when you’re paying 200 a night.  The sink in our bathroom was clogged, barely drained. I had to prop open the drain stopper to get the water to flow out. It made for a gross sink. There was not bathtub in the room, just a shower. Again hard when you have little kids. When we first got to our room there was no remote for the television. We had to call the front desk and have them bring us one. It took over an hour. Everything costs money here. Water is five dollars a bottle! I wish this hotel, especially in San Francisco, would install a water bottle refill station in the lobby, or on every floor. Pool and spa we’re closed due to covid, even though most pools in California are open now. Overall my stay here was just okay. Served its purpose, but wouldn’t stay here again.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: None
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes:
Rooms were not what you see in the pictures . They were old and outdated . Walls were thin.. you can hear anyone walking past or closing the doors .
This is not the worst.. Customer service was not the friendliest . I modified on booking.com to 2 nights from 4 nights with the rate of us367 shown on the app . It was approved .. But when I arrived late at night , the hotel insisted that I booked for 4 nights and wanted to charge me for 4 nights !!!! After hours wasted talking to booking.com , my booking was changed to 2 nights .. I thought my drama was over , but NO !!! The next thing i saw on booking.com app, my pricing was changed to us493 .. Seriously !!! I thought I should be paying only us367..
That was not all.. After checking out, the hotel charged me a whopping US1500 for a 2 night stay .. Imagine my horror and the funds being locked up on my prepaid card . I have to spend hours call booking.com and the frustration was that each time the customer service officer is different …. Some are really good and some are super lousy. you can’t get back the previous person who serviced you ..

And at the reception we could not get the relevant information about parking check out times - one guy told us that it is before 3pm, the lady in the morning told it is before 12, and then you will have to pay $40 more, which was again not relevant since at the parking lot there charge was indicated $50! reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Two Double Beds and City View
reviews_list.Review_Likes:
I booked two hotel rooms which are rooms 302 and 305. We checked in today at around 7 pm after a long drive from a road trip from LA with our 4 kids. My husband and I went out for a dinner in McCormick’s while our kids went out to stroll around Fisherman’s Wharf and after that went back to the hotel. They went first to the market besides the front desk to look around for some snacks to buy. The front desk lady already initiated rudeness towards them. When they were looking around, they were surprised to see her standing and watching them as if they are “thieves” or made them feel so uncomfortable enough. To make matters worst is while they still look around and try to ignore the “degrading” look from that front desk lady, she unbelievably knocked several times to the wooden door of the market to call their attention and said “ Are you buying or not??! Do you even have money to pay? And don’t touch anything! “
My kids were dumbfounded, surprised and felt humiliated. And this happened in the presence of other guests. They don’t have any idea why they were being treated that way. One of my daughters even witnessed a change of attitude when there was another guest who asked the front desk lady to hold her bag while she grabs something from the market and she warmly accepted the request while they were treated differently. MiSTREATED. HUMILIATED. DISCRIMINATED.
I and my husband went back to the hotel after celebrating my birthday dinner night so happy and to return to the hotel to see our kids so distraught about what happened, totally ruined everything. We addressed this complaint right away to the manager, Cris, as soon as we were told what happened by our kids. We went straight down to the front desk with our daughter and confronted the front desk lady who mistreated and discriminated them. She called the manager Cris. My daughter even said that Cris saw them when they went to the market earlier.

reviews_list.Review_Likes:
Zimmer waren groß und komfortabel eingerichtet. Couch, Tisch, relativ großer Kühlschrank für eigene Getränke.
Das Bad war ebenfalls groß und mit begehbarer Dusche ausgestattet. Erfreulich waren die vielen, dicken weißen Handtücher und allerhand nützliche gute Necessaires (Seifen, Cremen, Öl, Duschgel usw.)
Während unseres 10tägigen Aufenthalts hat es leider zwischendurch mal geregnet und man ist gerne in diesem Zimmer geblieben. 
Lage ist ist für die Stadt ideal. Erstmal mit Taxi oder Auto gut zu erreichen und später kann man die Stadt gut zu Fuß erkunden. Restaurants, Supermärkte gleich um die Ecke.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Wir haben uns in diesem Hotel sehr wohl gefühlt. Die Ausstattung der Zimmer war gut, es war alles vorhanden was wir gebraucht haben. Der Service vor allem an der Rezeption war hervorragend! Die Mitarbeiterin hat uns direkt ein Zimmer in Pool Nähe gegeben aufgrund unser Kinder. Das fand ich sehr aufmerksam. Auch fand ich es hervorragend das die Mitarbeiter uns hilfsbereit überall entgegen kamen wo es nur möglich war. Das hat mich sehr beeindruckt!! Die nette Dame im Restaurant war sehr freundlich und hilfsbereit!! Ich fand das echt Klasse wie liebevoll sie uns bedient hat!! Ein super Service auch dort!!

reviews_list.Review_Likes: L'emplacement été parfait, la chambre plutôt correct.
Hotel je na jako dobroj lokaciji, uredan je, čist i ugodan za boravak. Osoblje je ljubazno. U sobi smo imali mali aparat za kavu.
总体来看很好
muy bueno, regresaré ya que tiene una excelente ubicación
emplacement, le jacuzzi après une grande journée de visite.

Te obligan a pagar un destination fee de 30 USD que no vale la pena, incluye bicicletas gratis pero son muy pocas (6) y cuando quisimos usarlas la respuesta fue que alguien se había llevado la llave del candado que las aseguraba, los descuentos que ofrecen tienen mucha letra menuda y no los utiliza uno nunca, hay una opción de parqueadero más barata a 2 cuadras de ahí contratada por el propio hotel, es 18 dólares/día más barata que la que te ofrece el valet parking del hotel que es un verdadero robo (62 USD/día), el hotel es bonito y buen situado, en general me pareció muy caro para lo que ofrecen, cobran la marca.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Basic Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Very clean and super friendly staff! Would come back again!

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: I love the location very convenient and easy to get here from SFO Airport by taking BART. Close to Hop On Hop Off Tour Bus and Cable Car Station.  Owner is very welcoming and friendly staffs. Reasonable price.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: It's an old building so you can hear noises especially from the 2nd floor and bed is noisy.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Staff is really nice at Luz Hotel. Location is rather central. the hotel is very safe. the area also is safe for my standards, but there is visible poverty on some streets in the area. If that is a problem for you, avoid Ellis and O'Farrell St, and stick to Geary St, for example when taking BART train from airport and getting off at Powell. Little Saigon is very close, and there are several very good cheap Vietnamese restaurants. Bike-sharing bikes can easily be found nearby the Luz Hotel.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The employees are very helpful, directly gave us Tipps for our stay in San Francisco which where really helpful. Also the storing of our luagge befor and after check-in worked perfectly.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: No Breakfast offered, on the streets it we had a quite insecure feeling, but the Hotel itself is gated and save.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Welcoming staff. Cozy. Near Cable Cars.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Deluxe Double Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: the place
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: outside  plenty homeless

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Garden View
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Location, close to Union Square
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Would like to have had a breakfast option

reviews_list.Room_Type: Deluxe Double Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Perfect for solo travellers who don't plan on staying in the hotel all day.comfy beds,clean toilets and showers. Location is good.room is small but it was enough if you are onlythere for sightseeing.staff are very friendly and helpful
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The street it was on was not the best but it was close to a lot of places to see.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: Ver is wonderful and very professional.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: I loved the location. Not far from Union Square.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Walls are very thin and some guests don’t take into consideration there are other people there (not the hotels fault).

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Owners were exceptionally friendly, very helpful and always up for a nice chat.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Superior Single Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: i was a solo traveler on budget, it suites my neat. the hitel is quit old but the room and baths is reall nice
reviews_list.Review_Likes: the room was nice and cozy
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: the streets have some homeless and addicts around. i didnt not bother to go out eitherway

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: It was great, I totally recommend it!
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The manager was amazing! He helped us park the car and also gave us a map about the most common places in the city. Also in the last day they gave us a little souvenir! Very thoughtful :)
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Ir was everything fine for me.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Deluxe Double Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Kind staff
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: No parking. Not the most comfortable bed. No private bathroom.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Staff were extremely friendly and helpful. Very central location and the bed was clean.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The insulation wasn't great so you could hear everything from the corridor or other rooms. Whilst it was clean, it was very worn and my room didn't look like the photo.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: Fair place to sleep in San Francisco
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Good location and very friendly staff
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The temperature inside the room/hallway/bathrooms was pretty cold and it was not the cleanest hotel I’ve seen

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: the owner was really friendly and helpful. the beds are fairly comfortable for the SF prices. It was nice and quiet
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: shower takes some time to properly warm up. the area is full of homeless people so location is not too safe for solo women travellers

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Staff and owner were very helpful and personable, access able 24hrs. Angle Deli/Cafe across the road great for early coffee and danish
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: While the location is very close (couple of blocks) to the center business district, which is great for exploring, those couple of blocks have a lot homeless living on the street. However this was common in Central SF.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: Good value and access to San Francisco with friendly staff.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The room was comfortable, clean, and secure.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The area was somewhat dangerous at night

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: it was good thanks to very nice and helpful staff
reviews_list.Review_Likes: the staffs
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: the room is old, a bit rundown. the neighborhood doesn’t seem to be safe and quite dirty

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Convenient room and location. Staff very friendly. Clean facilities.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: None

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: easy place to stay couple days and good location
reviews_list.Review_Likes: the staff. nicest staff I ever bump into!! no doubt

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: great budget option in convenient location and feels like home . Loved it.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: first of all was greeted by the owner, who was so lovely, made me feel very welcome, advised on how to best spend my few days in san francisco, gave me map, advise what to do and where not to go. The room was very clean, quiet and felt warm (in a good way). shared bathroom and toilet were very clean and not too many people sharing with. The hotel was 10 min walk to Union square and just slightly more to the closest train station (there direct train to the airport) so very easy commute.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: everything was great

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Luz Hotel is nearby Union Square, in a point that allow you to visit the most common places by walking (anyway there is the bus stop just opposite the hotel). Personally, I visited the city by walking. The staff were amazing! They gave me a map of the city and explained me the places that I could visit! I really appreciated everything!
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Everything is fine for me!

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Place is really old but still in good maintenance. Rooms and bathrooms are clean. Close to downtown and main connections. Owner and employees are friendly and caring. Price is equal to all the conditions.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: location staff and comfort

reviews_list.Room_Type: Basic Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The staff were incredibly nice and accommodating.  I really appreciated everything they did to make my stay comfortable.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: i got help from Ver and the rest of the staff with any questions or concerns I had. Will definitely look forward to goin
reviews_list.Review_Likes: it was very clean and the hospitality is the best I’ve ever had

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Amazing staff! I really felt welcome and at home. It was really nice for a woman who travels by herself to be staying at such a welcoming place! I could never thank you enough. Definitely the best place I stayed in San Fran. I was provided everything, clean towels, robes, soap, water and even a heater. There was even a smartTV with Netflix, YouTube and everything. At the end of my stay they even gave me a pen as a souvenir from the hotel. The shower and the bathroom were always super clean and very comfortable, I didn't even mind that they were shared. The location is really good, I could do anything nearby and it is safe, very close to union square and Powell Station. it took me 30min to go to places with public transportation from there. The best part, for me, was that the manager speaks Portuguese, and since I'm Brazilian, I felt even more welcome. Wish I had stayed longer, can't wait to come back! Thank you for the amazing service!

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Garden View
reviews_list.Main_Review: It's the best that you get in downtown SF for this number of stars hotel
reviews_list.Review_Likes: It's the best you can expect for this hotel accomodation style, the people that work in there are very kind and helpfull
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: It's on the verge of the tenderloin zone which is not reccomended at all in SF

reviews_list.Room_Type: Basic Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Nice staff.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: We found a cockroach in our room and there was a lot of spiderweb in the ceiling.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Superior Single Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Free wifi was a good service which helped meGood location in the mid of the city
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: No heating in the bedroomVery uncomfortable room for the showersToo high price for the overall service

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Garden View
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Location is not bad
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: This is the first time I booked a place with shared bathroom and rest room probably I shouldn’t have. the reviews on booking.com website weren't bad so I booked it. The first sight of the place shocked me with a shabby locked grille door, narrow, small hallway and dirty carpet, the reception is a tiny window and the room is the same size as the prison cell I visited on Alcatraz trip. When I opened the door to my assigned room, a strong sweat smell greeted me and I told the staff about it and asked for an air refresher and he brought me a fabric spray for the purpose. As a Chinese, I drink boiled water but there is no jug in the room so I asked for one and the staff hurriedly sorted out one coffee maker which he apparently washed hurriedly but still have heavy stains which I tried to wash off in my 5 nights stay but couldn’t get rid of. Apparently the staff tried to make things better for me although they don’t have enough resources of equipment or such. The place is so old and dirty so I feel very uncomfortable and tried not to touch anything. Staff are nice but it can not changed the fact that the place is substandard even by 3rd world country standard. The budget price doesn’t  mean such a poor facility is OK.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Deluxe Double Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: dirty, smells really bad

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: the people are great, ver was helpful rediscovering the area and albert was very nice
It was OK for the price. Centrally located downtown. The reception is very friendly.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Around there are many homeless and drug addicts, but they didnt bother me nor were somehow approaching me.

reviews_list.Review_Likes:
very good location, a nice and comfortable little room.
I absolutely recommend it, especially if it’s just for a couple of days.
Just keep in mind that you share toilets and the shower, they are not in the room but that didn’t bother me.
The staff is super friendly and extremely helpful.

The people at the front desk were absolutely amazing. They are definitely the strongest asset of this hotel. They were the most welcoming people I've met in a while and they were making sure everything was fine with every occasion.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The location in not the best because of all the homeless people in the area. Near this hotel, the situation is not that bad, but still not advisable to walk around during the night, especially alone. Also, the rooms could use some refurbishment, but it was not unpleasant.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Nice Staff - helpful and friendly
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Neighborhood was very rough - a lot of homeless. You get what you pay for. Small rooms. Stains on the towels and sheets.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: 위치가 다운타운 인근 게어리 st에 있어서 너무 좋았습니다. 그 근방에 이만한 가격의 숙소를 찾아보기 힘들어요. 직원들도 친절해요.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Deluxe Double Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes:
Das Hotel ist sehr zentral gelegen, in der Nähe des 
Union Square. Viele Restaurants sind fußläufig und auch 
mit dem Auto kommt man schnell überall hin. Das Hotel
befindet sich in einem sehr alten Gebäude, was man der 
Einrichtung auch ansieht - dennoch ist alles sehr sauber. 
Das absolute Highlight ist der Host - der Hotelmanager ist 
sehr zuvorkommend und freundlich. Er hat uns sogar einen 
Parkplatz vor dem Haus reserviert, uns einen ausgiebigen 
Plan an Aktivitäten in SF ausgestellt und angeboten, einen 
seiner Mitarbeiter loszuschicken um uns etwas zu Essen 
zu holen, als wir am Abend der Anreise zu müde waren, 
noch auszugehen. Wir haben uns sehr wohl gefühlt.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Single Room with Shared Bathroom

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Sehr freundliche Vermieter. Der Union Square und die Powell-Station sind in Laufweite. Gemütliche Zimmer, die Toiletten und die Duschen sehr sauber. Gegenüber beim Angel Cafe und Deli gibt es sehr leckere Frühstücksbagel.

Los baños y duchas compartidos estaban limpios y prolijos.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (10-12 Bed) Mixed dorm Room

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (6-9 Bed) Female Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Location was very nice if you prefer nature and greenery. Staff allowed me to check in early
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: No individual light and electric socket on each bed. I have stayed in many hostels, both HI and non-HI, both within the US and outside of the USA. What I noticed is that employees don't help you with your luggage, even if you are the only guest checking in or out. You have to make and unmake your bed. I understand this is not a hotel, but a helping hand is greatly appreciated.Helping others wouldn't hurt

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (6-9 Bed) Female Only Dorm Room

reviews_list.Review_Likes: I love the view and the little theater.  I liked the computer that they used to have in the lobby that you could use because I am the last person on earth who has a flip phone without internet. I hope they bring it back. reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Would be nice to have a bit of a privacy shield near the heads of the beds and bed lights like many hostels have. Also better signage to get from the street to there. Luckily I memorized the way to walk from the flagpole in the dark.

my room is private room for 2 peoples and 3 peoples but share bathrooms and toilets with other peoples. Cleanliness is ok and acceptable when compare with price and all convenience.

Perfect location: a room with a view to the Alcatraz. Unique atmosphere. Clean and tidy everywhere. A small basic breakfast offered for free
 (coffee, bread, fruits).
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Our room was really small and a bit noisy - you could hear people talking in the lobby and in corridors. Ventilation not working very well.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (6-9 Bed) Male Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: excellent place to stay i recommended happily.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: the view from the hostel is perfect : golden bridge and alcatraz.the breakfast is very good and all the staff member are nice. the room are clean and well thinking. you have everything you need for a short stay and also for a long one.the place is quiet i night and you can sleep well.you can go everywhere in san francisco easily from the hostel.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: nothing

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (10-12 Bed) Mixed dorm Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: value for money, tucked away not far from city in beautiful location
reviews_list.Review_Likes: the beds are comfortable, it’s a beautiful location overlooking the bridge and Alcatraz - short walk to the marina area which is lovely as well as fisherman’s wharf , where you can get on a cable car up to the main area. the staff are really friendly and caring - there’s also plenty of hostel events you can go to at their sister hostel eg. bar crawl. like that there’s a full kitchen and fridge so you can prepare your own meals
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: didn’t like that the showers weren’t enclosed cubicles you could shower and get changed in in privacy. I thought there would be more available at breakfast - was just bread, spreads, cold boiled eggs and cereal. also there’s not PowerPoints for charging your phone inside the room which makes it tricking charging in the public area.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (6-9 Bed) Female Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: A super hostal with nice welcome and good vibes overlooking the Golden Gate Bridge. Very accommodating staff at the reception, open to all questions, very helpful. I especially liked the stylish wooden decor and the cozy lounge next to the reception. The location is situated in a park and perfect for exploring San Francisco (bus stations within 10 min. walking distance). One of the best hostals I have ever stayed in. Value for money better than many other hotels in SF.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (6-9 Bed) Male Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Love this place as it is usually good and old San Frisco. Rents cheap and if you're lucky you get a 👍 room.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Nice place

reviews_list.Room_Type: Family Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: location. Excellent staff

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (6-9 Bed) Female Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: absolutely loved the location, you can see the golden gate bridge from outside the hostel; the staff were all really friendly and helpful
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: the dorm beds don’t come with individual sockets and reading light

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Small (4-5 Bed) Female Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: would stay again . very easy to get to from SFO by BART train to Powell 10 usd and bus 30 2.50 usd pick up Geary and Kea
reviews_list.Review_Likes:
excellent fantastic location , views overlooking Golden Gate Bridge and Alcatraz . very clean including communal bathrooms and showers - they are also separate ie female and male, very into recycling - well done 
easy to get to by public transport, free wifi good, free breakfast (though better in previous stay at downtown hi hostel with cream cheese and bagels ) and good cooking facilities and large fridges to put your food safely 
close by to fisherman’s wharf and pier 39 as well as short walk to Blazing saddles where you can rent a bike for the day  (@40 usd) to cycle across golden gate bridge to Saucilito and further to red woods (mostly flat- highly recommend that for a day) 
bed mattress  is plastic covered so I took along a mattress protector to put under my bed sheet and very comfortable to sleep
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes:
after dark, walk up from Bay Street where there are lights, do no walk up hill by harbour as pitch black , especially if on your own, 
beds - there were no ladders on bunk beds so difficult and dangerous to climb up and down , especially in dark at night . I had a bottom bunk thankfully 
no bed lights - whereas downtown hostel (stayed last time) there are partitions and individual lights on each bed which is good if you want to read after room  light is off
shared bathroom with everyone and no ensuite bathroom for 4 bed female to share with just room - there are in downtown Hi hostel (but location not nearly so good) 
no alcohol allowed so could not easily have a beer or glass of wine with an evening meal you made .

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Small (4-5 Bed) Female Only Dorm Room

reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The cafe wasn't open and there weren't any socials to get to know people.

reviews_list.Main_Review: We had a private room and it was great
reviews_list.Review_Likes: We really enjoyed our stay overall. I think they really try to provide everything they can to make you feel comfortable. Wi-Fi worked nicely, water stations available, a lot of common areas (which we didnt use but I can imagine they can be amazing for people traveling solo!). The view from our small private room was also great
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: They focus a lot on sustainability and stressed the issue with the draught in California a lot by telling you not to waste water and yet for the free breakfast they did not have ANY plant based milk option whatsover. Cow's milk wastes even more water than almond milk (if you don't believe it, look up actual studies) because of how much water it takes to raise the cow (for the cow to drink and to clean the cow and the areas it occupies) but also to grow the crops to feed the cow. So I was shocked to see they were only offering cow's milk. I realize it's a free breakfast and I'm not expecting much, just a plant based milk option such as oat milk which is much more sustainable than cow's milk. Disappointing.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (6-9 Bed) Female Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: Good spot for a short stay in San Fran
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Location is EXCELLENT. In a beautiful park on a hill, you can see the Golden Gate Bridge on days with no fog, and you can very easily walk towards the piers (Marine Park), Fisherman's Wharf, and Pier 39. House itself is quite spacious, with a large common area, and it didn't feel cramped.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The mattresses in the dorm were terrible; strangely so soft that you sunk immediately down into them (no structure at all) and SO NOISY. You literally couldn't move without the crinkling noise making a ruckus which sucks in a dorm where everyone might be sleeping at different times. I was on the top bunk and climbing up there and settling in without trying to disturb others was basically impossible. The dorm rooms were also pretty cramped (to be expected I suppose), though there were roomy under-bed storage lockers (bring your own lock). Whole room smelled a little bit, but with the windows open it was ok.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Small (4-5 Bed) Female Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: Great location, worth the other inconveniences
reviews_list.Review_Likes:
1. You cannot beat the location. I could see the Golden Gate Bridge and Alcatraz Island from my window. It's a very nice, short walk to Beach Street and to Gharadellis ice-cream, amongst other things.
2. Pool table
3. Outdoor courtyard with comfortable seating
4. The cleaning staff are lovely
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes:
1. If you are on your own, try not to arrive at night/in the dark. It's up a secluded dark hill, but it's fine in the day. The hostel could do with having signage on the road and lane, but there was nothing. 
2. Café was closed and no free breakfast - maybe they just need to get back up to speed after being closed for Covid
3. No ladder to top bunks (room 22). I mentioned to staff, but this was not rectified. I thought all the top bunks didn't have ladders, but  then saw some top bunks in other rooms did have ladders. This was very annoying, as I hurt my feet clambering up the front of the bed
4. Avoid rooms 22-24 because you need to walk through the common room each time to go to toilet, have a shower, go to kitchen etc.
5. Staff go through your stuff in the communal fridge and confiscate alcohol. Not a problem for me, but some travellers were not happy
6. Strange vibe, not as relaxed as I'd hoped - maybe too many rules? 
7. It's difficult to keep windows open. We had to use books and plastic bottles to keep windows open 
8. The discount you get on bike rental is not a discount. The saving that the bike rental company offers is 'donated' to the hostel.
Having said all this, I'd stay again. The location is second to none. Downtown is definitely a place to avoid, a lot of drunks and shouters.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Medium (6-9 Bed) Female Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Location is great! Staff is friendly
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: There was no breakfast even though the listing said there was so you pay for something you do not get. Women’s bathrooms are in disrepair!Mattresses are old and worn out and extremely uncomfortable.  Kitchen electrical is questionable and there was no electric for the weekend in the kitchen. No maintenance staff on call on the weekend and front desk staff not trained to change out a fuse.There is no alcohol allowed on the premises.There is no quiet private area. Windows have not been cleaned in years.Trouble getting hot water in showers and hot/cold labels reversed. When booking site said it required vaccination. Not true! You also get an email that vaccination status will be checked which also was a lie. Felt they lied to you to fill beds. Front desk staff kept telling people they could do laundry starting at 3pm when signage in the laundry room says 4:30pm.There are no vending machines and the cafe listed an amenity on their site has been closed. Again, felt lied to.Not enough space to for your belongings to store. The boxes under the beds are too small and open the wrong way so the lid slams down on your hands as you are trying to get things out. No place to place things like glasses etc at night. Not enough electrical outlets in rooms and no extension cords.

Location is great, one hour of really relaxing walk  will get you to the golden gate bridge, 40 minutes to get to the center or pier 39 and famous food places. Staff is really friendly and helpful.
Overall it’s an ok place if you travel single, if you’re a couple or more people - I’d recommend going for the hotel room with some privacy and amenities, price won’t be so different for more then 1 person i  the room.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes:
It’s very noisy compared to other hostels i’ve been to. Quite hours are from 11pm till 7am, however both nights that I stayed there were still people gathering quite loudly in the lounge after 11pm.
Wind blows through even closed windows, which is really uncomfortable. I asked to change bed to be away from, personal had no issue, which is great, however on the opposite side of the room bed was shaking from all the walking in the corridors.
Also mattresses are extremely soft, you basically sink in them.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Standard Queen Room

reviews_list.Review_Dislikes:
The staff was unfortunately not so kind, I think it's a minimum to just welcome a guest, or say BACK a 'good morning', we tried for two days with no succeed, maybe everyone had a bad day... anyway, never really experienced a hosting like this in the US,  a little smile and kindness would be great :) 
One other, what is definetely not the hostel's fault, but good to know, that you will be withing earshot of the foghorns. So there can be days/mornings, when you hear them (I mean very loud horns, you wake up for them) from there. One of our morning started at 4.30 AM, because it lasted for 2 hours, and heard in every second minute, so earplugs are recommended.

O banheiro comunitário é constantemente limpo, não tive problemas para usar. Chuveiro com água quente e boa pressão. Funcionários super simpáticos e solícitos. Tem lavanderia e os preços para uso de máquina e secadora eram em conta.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Me gustó todo! El personal en recepción fue siempre muy amable y predispuesto. Hablan inglés y español, y ponen música en todos los idiomas y culturas :). Las personas alojadas en el hostel también fueron muy cálidas! Tocaban el piano durante la noche, y se formaban grupos de gente disfrutando. La ubicación es increíble! Está ubicado en Fort Mason, en Fisherman’s Wharf, y es súper cómodo para caminar por el área hasta el pier 39. Desde la ventana de mi habitación se veía Alcatraz!El hostel incluye sábanas y toallas. Hay lavandería, se puede comprar el jabón en recepción. Lo mejor es que incluía también el desayuno: café, leche, cereales, pan, manteca, peanut butter, mermelada, pancakes, bananas. Había tostadora en la cocina. Las áreas comunes son muy lindas! El ambiente es muy acogedor y te invita a socializar. También me pareció muy interesante ver personas de todas las edades, y familias enteras alojándose. No lo había visto en otros hostels en los que estuve y me encantó la experiencia.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Das Hostel befindet sich in einer tollen Lage. Aus der großen Küche heraus hat man einen tollen Blick auf Alcatraz und die Piers sind in der Nähe mit kaum einer halben Stunde Fußweg zum Pier 39. Ein Safeway Supermarkt ist ziemlich direkt nebenan und die Busanbindung ist ebenfalls gut. Die Küche war absolut genial, es hat an nichts gemangelt. Zahlreiche Herdplatten, Industriegrill, neue Pfannen, Geschirr, Besteck, Utensilien, Gewürze ... Zudem gab es, auch wenn das Frühstück weiterhin ausgesetzt war, morgens Kaffee. Preise zum Waschen sehr fair (1$ Waschen, 1$ Trocknen, 0,75$ Waschmittel). Alles war sehr sauber. Schließfächer unter dem Bett riesig, es passt ein großer Koffer rein und es ist trotzdem noch Platz vorhanden.

Un lugar que genera sentimientos contradictorios. Por un lado, tiene muchos defectos. Por otro, es un sitio histórico, y en consecuencia no admite muchas reformas.
Como lugar histórico, es impresionante realmente.
Quiero destacar la buena actitud y ayuda del personal de la mañana, en recepción y en limpieza. Sufrí un percance personal y me lo solucionaron con excelente buena disposición. Realmente me sacaron de un problema.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: L'ambiance était particulièrement sympathique. Les lieux de détente et de repas (avec une grande cuisine et tous les ustensils) très spacieux, beaucoup de réfrigérateurs et de casiers pour stocker les aliments. Mes voisines de lit étaient toutes très agréables et respectueuses. L'auberge se trouve tout à côté de l'océan dans un coin de verdure, et est juste à côté d'un arrêt de bus où plusieurs lignes s'arrêtent. On peut quasiment aller dans toutes les directions. Vraiment le lieu idéal pour visiter San Francisco à moindre frais.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Fantastisk beliggenhed i det historiske Fort Mason, et meget fredeligt område tæt på Fishermans Wharf og med flot udsigt.  Jo, det er lidt væk fra downtown, men så får man noget andet i stedet for.Jeg boede på eget værelse, hvilket er relativt dyrt, men med en god seng, flot udsigt (se billede) men uden bøjler eller skab. Jeg har været her for ca 5 år siden og er vild med beliggenhed og det store fællesrum med sofaer og gaspejs.

El hostel está en un edificio viejo muy chulo con unas vistas increíbles y muy cerca del muelle, lo malo es que al ser viejo huele mucho a humedad, parece que el sitio esta un poco dejado y es una pena porque el espacio tiene mucho potencial. Menos Kevin que fue muy amable, el resto del personal super desagradable, la chica rubia muy mala onda. A la noche mucho ruido. El café/restaurante que hay en el hostel también estaba cerrado.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Family Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes:
L' emplacement est extraordinaire! Je n' aurais pas pu choisir mieux; entouré d' un grand parc, près de l' eau, vue sur le Golden Bridge et Alcatraz et un sentier de marche ou de vélo qui nous mène aux Piers. L' hebergement est très propre, partout où l' on va même les salles de bain. Le petit déjeuner est apprécié, il y a un emplacement pour écouter des films et un autre salon pour la lecture ou pour y jouer de la musique. Le personnel est très gentil.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Habe (dank Gabriel) ein fabelhaftes Mehrbett-Zimmer bekommen, was ruhig gelegen war und einen super Ausblick auf Alcatraz und die Golden Gate Bridge hatte. Die Betten fand ich sehr bequem (die Matratzen sind sehr weich, aber ich liebe das). Für ein Hostel waren die Duschen außergewöhnlich sauber. Und das im Preis enthaltene Frühstück vergleichsweise vielfältig (Toast, (Erdnuss-)Butter, Marmelade, Ei, Haferflocken, Cornflakes, Pancakes, Banane, Apfel und Kaffee). reviews_list.Review_Likes:
Das Personal war super freundlich und konnte uns jederzeit helfen. Die Zimmer und Bäder waren sehr sauber. Wir hatten ein Zimmer mit 4 Hochbetten und waren von 4 Nächten zwei Nächte ganz alleine und die restlichen zwei war das Zimmer auch nie voll. 
Die Küche hatte eine super Ausstattung zum selber kochen und zum Frühstück gab es Kaffee und Tee. Wir haben viele Gleichgesinnte getroffen die alles super hilfsbereit waren und coole Tips hatten. 
Die Lage des Hostels ist auch super. Man kommt zu Fuß zum Fisherman‘s Wharf und Pier 39. Bus- und Cable Car Stationen sind auch super nah.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in Small (4-5 Bed) Male Only Dorm Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: サンフランシスコのホテルはどこも宿泊費が高く、この都市特有の駐車場がない、部屋が狭い等がイメージとしてあげられると思いますが、このホステルには当てはまりません。というのも、このホステルは昔、病院だった建物をリニューアルしたとのことで、広い敷地の中にあります。駐車場はもちろん無料。敷地内からゴールデンゲートブリッジ、アラカトラズ島が見えます。徒歩圏内に名物のケーブルカー乗り場に行けます。スーパーマーケットも近くです。受付も24時間オープンです。スタッフもフレンドリー！チェックインで部屋を確認したところ、２段ベッドの上段だったので、下段にして欲しいといったところ、快く部屋を変更してくれました。因みに２段ベッドの上段は隙間が多く、はしごがないので怖いと思った次第です。最高の立地条件です。今、サンフランシスコにいるんだ！と実感できる宿です。

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Die Lage ist wirklich Bombe. Man sieht beim Frühstück sowohl die Golden Gate Bridge als auch Alcatraz; der Bus ist auch nicht weit entfernt. Durch die Einrichtung hat man im Hostel direkt den coolen San Francisco Vibe. Bringt aber unbedingt euer eigenes Vorhängeschloss für den Spind mit. Als ich morgens verschlafen auf dem Weg ins Bad war, meinte einer der Mitarbeiter ganz freundlich “Guten Morgen!” zu mir. Das hat mir direkt den Tag versüßt. Ich habe mich dort sehr wohl und sicher gefühlt. Beim nächsten Mal bleibe ich auf jeden Fall wieder dort! Klimaanlage gibt es in diesem historischen Gebäude übrigens nicht. Da es aber ohnehin ziemlich frisch und windig in San Francisco ist, reicht das Belüftungsgerät in jedem Zimmer und vorm Schlafen das Fenster ein Mal ordentlich öffnen vollkommen aus. Es gibt ein kostenloses Frühstück morgens. Ist nicht üppig, aber man hat zumindest etwas im Magen.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Die Lage ist sehr gut. Man erreicht den Hafen direkt zu Fuß. Das Personal ist freundlich, aber auch sehr streng. Für Menschen, denen es wichtig ist strenge Regeln auferlegt zu bekommen + Kontrollgänge, die gibt es hier. Ich kann nicht einschätzen, ob es notwendig ist.Das Hostel an sich ist sehr weitläufig und von der Geschichte her interessant- wirkt etwas wie ein Museum. Check-In 24h flexibel fand ich gut. Zum ausladen gibt es auch einen Parkplatz direkt vor der Türe. Tatsächlich befinden sich rund um das Hostel ausnahmsweise mal keine Homeless People, dass ist hier schon etwas besonderes! Für die, die viel wert auf Austausch legen. Der Aufenthaltsraum ist sehr groß. Er wird genutzt um mobile Devise mit Akku zu versorgen. Hier stehen auch Kabel zur Verfügung.

Un accueil agréable ! Endroit très bien situé et lieux très propre.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Friendly staff. Took care of my issues with no problem.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: Close to the tourist areas. Safe to sleep in.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: It's all about location. It's close to Fisherman's Wharf. It's right on Columbus and Lombard (the famous crooked street in SF), so it's easy to get to ALL the tourist areas . The people were pretty nice, always smiling.Te room has a flatscreen, a fridge, a microwave oven and a sink. It's right next to/in Little Italy, so lots of great neighborhood restaurants.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: It's a below average stay. Although the sheets were clean, the pillow cases could have used a bit of bleach. But you get what you pay for. The windows dont really close, so if you happen to be there over the weekend, there's a comedy club and the line to get in is right under your window.It's good to book if you only need a place to sleep for a few hours and explore the city the rest of the time.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: Ideal for 2 night stay to see wharf area of city.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Location was great.  .  There was a fridge and a microwave in room. Bed was comfy and room was clean
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: TV didnt work and no tea/coffee making in the room. No dining of any type in hotel.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Room was small but clean and quiet.  Very nice location. Fine for 2 nights and price.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Bathroom and shower in hallway need more attention from staff.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Central location, conveniently accessible from airport too.The room is not small, has sink, fridge and microwave, TV stand can be used as a table. The bed was good.Window can be opened for ventilation.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The hotel is not so clean, strange odor sometimes. Toilets have ho sink to wash hands. Some toilets are combined with shower, so need to bring your soap to wash hands. In my room there were no racks for clothes and for towel, probably lost long time ago.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: Nice location, good for spending one or too nights. The restrooms can be improved.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The location was great, the room was big enough for just one person. Easy check in and chec out.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The restrooms too small and not too many for so many rooms. No sinks at the toilets.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Clean and good location.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The staff is really helpful. The location is excellent. The value is great!

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: This review has been hidden because it doesn't meet our guidelines.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: the location was perfect. you have everything around you. almost felt like we were going in circles while sight seeing. I would totally recommend this place if you’re on a budget or last minute booking. parking is a struggle though!
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: staff was doing everything they can to keep the shared bathrooms clean but no one really cared to keep it clean. (you can tell men there wouldn’t lift up the seat to pee) pretty much it. everything else was clean, check in was easy, no deposit fee. and they were able to check us in early.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: Not bad of a place but the  people are very nice and helpful
reviews_list.Review_Likes: I like the  room
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: It was different the frist time to share a bathroom with other people who lives there.  The people were nice and very helpful 🙂

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: You get what you pay for
reviews_list.Review_Likes: You get what you pay for. Accomodation is half hotel rooms and half social housing. Room was ok, it has a sink for hand washing and brushing teeth. There was also a fridge and microwave which helped with storing food and microwaving meals. The staff at the desk were very nice and answered every question I had. They allowed me to store my bags there after checkout the day I left. Area is very central with a cable car stop 2 metres away from the door. 10 min walk to fisherman's wharf and plenty of amenities within walking distance.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Bathrooms were down the hallway and some were quite dirty with mould on the shower curtains or no curtain at all. Very strange smell in much of the building.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Main_Review: This is where one stays if poverty and despair are approaching.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: They had smoking rooms.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Double Room with Shared Bathroom
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Absolutely fantastic, kind and helpful staff!
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: I wish the hotel invested more in cleaning their shared facilities.

reviews_list.Main_Review: Nap York Pacific Heights is great!
reviews_list.Review_Likes: I love the space, the comfortable beds and the staff.Everything is so calm and relaxing and the music is very soothing, which is always great in a place to rest. Nap York is close to most places I've visited in the area, and transportation is very easily accessible.

reviews_list.Room_Type: 1 Economy Class Pod in 6 Bed Female Dorm
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Best night's sleep I've had my entire trip. The mattress was super comfy, and the barriers and curtains were great in blocking out light and giving some privacy in the shared room. The room was large and spacious, and the whole space was so clean the entire stay. There were ample bathrooms and showers so you were never kept waiting. I would stay here again in a heartbeat.

reviews_list.Main_Review: Best hostel in my USA trip !
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Loved this place, especially the staff! Travelers were so nice too! Thanks guys for welcoming me and kindness and food hehe!
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Be sure to like stairs climbing - but thats quite all the city though.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes:
Oh man, this is by far my best ever hostel experience!
The best location, the best staff, the best comfort, the best roommates, they have it all.
Apart from the usual things like cleanliness, amenities and all where the hostel checks all marks, there were a few things I was concerned about before booking -
=> I've 3 bags will it be comfortable or not.
While I was staying only 2 - 5 beds out of 8 in my room were occupied, so there was plenty of room for me. Even when full it has huge lockers that can have your backpacks inside and you can keep your trolley bag besides your bed.
=> There are too many stairs.
The quiet dorm is on the third floor (second floor for me as I am used to having the ground floor as floor zero back home) which wasn't too many stairs at all. There are also chairs placed on every floor in case you need a breather before heading up.
=> Being an introvert will I be able to talk to people and spend good time in the city since I know no one there.
A great aspect of this hostel is that most of the staff are volunteers and they are world travelers themselves. Which brings about a totally different perspective and it makes it so easier to have conversations with them.
=> What do I do in the city
The hostel folks have so many interesting activities planned for each day of the week, that you'll definitely find something to do. They have an answer to almost all your touristy queries.
=> I'm traveling in Thanksgiving week and I don't have friends here. What would I do?
The hostel manager (who's a gem of a person himself) and the staff arranged an amazing Thanksgiving dinner for us all. Made me feel like I was sitting among friends that I've known for so long and made my stay memorable.
If people at the hostel are reading this, thank you so much for all that you do!
Hoping to run into you amazing folks someday somewhere soon!
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Why did I just stay for only 4 nights!

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: The Pacific Tradewinds Hostel provided me a great place to stay in San Francisco on a budget.
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The Hostel is kept very clean. It is on the third and fourth floor of an old building without an elevator. The interior space must have been recently rehabilitated and so the bathrooms and showers are modern. The staff is very friendly. There is a bus stop one block away, Bart station six blocks from the hostel, and a small Japanese eatery next door which offers very reasonably priced yet substantial lunch specials, the Tokyo Express.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The bed could have been more comfortable to sleep in.

reviews_list.Review_Likes: Everyone and everything I encountered here were absolutely fine.  I would highly recommend to all sorts of travelers for short- and long-term stays.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Arrived early and they had everything ready to go for me so I didn't have to lug my gear around town all afternoon. Got a great recommendation from the on-site host to visit Delores Park, which was better than I could have imagined. prepared an awesome dinner and they had everything you could need. Plus, the other guest were very friendly and easy to get along with. 12/10 would stay again!!. I did appreciate their approach to COVID-19. Very clean and responsibly following protocols, but remained friendly and accessible.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Not one thing was an issue.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Very friendly, kind, helping staff, very friendly guests. No need to bring towel, soap, breakfast. 2x per week even dinner is served for free.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Lock for guest lockers are available only for purchase. No free locks. The lockers are not the most comfortable to use as they are on the floor.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: Great vives, great location and really worth the money!
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The activities organised by the hostel team, the location and the vibe of the hostel itself. The team really did make this experience and they are very successful at making the hostel feel like a home away from home!
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: The number of stairs you have to climb to get to reception hahah! Very typical of San Francisco. The bathrooms for the top floor dorm rooms were also just off of the common room which means using the facilities is quite public. You have to walk through the common areas and kitchen when needing a shower/the bathroom - not a critism, the building layout is the layout. It's simply a personal preference to have a little more privacy.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: Overall great stay for the price paid in San Fran!
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Staff are super helpful and clearly love what they do. The complimentary breakfast in the morning was great as well and the BBQ on Friday nights. Lots of activities on offer by the hostel and they are a great resource for more info of things to do in the city. Beds were comfy and the lockers under each bed were huge. Charging ports for each bed were also helpful. Right around the corner from Chinatown from some great meals and a short walk from North Beach for tons of options to eat and drink. Very walkable location for the whole city!
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: Light and noise from the street were a bit intrusive, but to be expected when staying in an old building in the city (nothing earplugs and an eye mask won’t fix). Showers and toilets on the second floor of the hostel were a bit cramped but I was told there were others that were bigger.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Main_Review: Not the best one but they try
reviews_list.Review_Likes: The staff were kind and helpful and the location is central. The breakfast is a bonus even if it is just toasts, eggs and coffee. It is still more than you would normally get in hostels.
reviews_list.Review_Dislikes: I sent message earlier asking about something but never got an answer. Rooms are too small for 8 beds. You do find places with 4 dorm beds pretty much for the same size cheaper in SF. Everyones stuff was laying around in the room so it was hard to even walk so you would not step on someones laptop etc. Although there seems to be lockers under the bed it was impossible to get hold of those because of the sheer amount of stuff scattered everywhere. I know this is not hostel's fault when people are messy but maybe letting guests know about the lockers and encouraging them to use those might be a good idea. I don't know how the rooms can ever be cleaned because of this but the place didn't seem dirty just a little run down. I didn't get much of a tour of the place so I had to figure out where the towels and even the toilets/shower where. The communal space gets cramped as well but hey at least it is way to meet people when you do have to share the table with others.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: por el precio muy cómodo y los chavos que atiendes son muy amables adiciónal las actividades que hacen a diario para que los huéspedes se conozcan se agradece

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Todo perfecto. Todo el mundo fue super agradable y muy acogedor.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Super quartier plein centre, lieu chaleureux et cuisine bien équipée, chambre relativement calme (on n'entendait rien venant de la rue !), staff très cool, et tout était propre.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: L'ambiance etait excellente, comme une bande de collocataires. Le rooftop est magnifique

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Todo, me pareció completo en todos los aspectos

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Clima legal entre hóspedes e funcionários. Localização.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Une vraie auberge de jeunesse avec des vraies rencontres.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: El staff, el desayuno y las actividades que realiza el staff.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Ce que j’ai le plus apprécié c’est la convivialité de l’auberge. Chaque le soir, le personnel organise un événement (soirée film, soirée barbecue, tacos,…). Ces événements permettent de faire connaissance avec les autres voyageurs et de faire de supers rencontres.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: La gente que trabaja ahi, como los que se hospedan. Todos hacen que sea un ambiente familiar y muy agradable para estar. Los servicios y la Ubicación. La ciudad es excelente para recorrerla a pie, y la locacion del hostel es muy util.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: В 6 местном номере было три человека. Есть кухня, где можно готовить самим в течении дня, утром завтрак - яичницу готовишь сам, банан, чай, кофе, молоко, кажется были хлопья. При заселении парень на ресепшене дал карту, подробно объяснил куда сходить, что посмотреть, куда не стоит ходить, очень помог этим

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: El staff, siempre atentos a lo que necesites y con muy buena onda. Algunos detalles como toallas, shampoo y otras cosas que se pueden usar suman mucho. La ubicación es muy a mano de todo.

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: ambiente multicultural

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: l’accueil, le personnel, l’ambiance

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Me encanto el trato familiar que tienen en el hostel, me he encontrado con mucha gente muy buena ahi, me lo he pasado genial, me encantaron las noches de barbacoa, las tardes de tacos😁, las excursiones hacia Golden Gate Bridge and Golden Gate park, el personal muy maj@s, los desayunos basicos pero buenos, todo fue genial, gracias😊!

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: Todo lo que necesitas como backpacker! Muy buena ubicación, es lo que más me gusto!Muy buena onda en el hostel! Buenas duchas, buena cama, enchufes a la mano y toallas que puedes cambiar todos los días!

reviews_list.Room_Type: Bed in 8-Bed Mixed Dormitory Room
reviews_list.Review_Likes: convivial , bon emplacement , très propre
